Control statement
-------------------
The statement or instructions are used to inform the computer to perform the task when program is being executed.
There are 4 types of control statement : 
a. Sequential control statement 
   input ------ process --------- output
         (Formula Implementation)
   ex: p,r,t   si=(p*r*t)/100     o/p : si

b. Conditional control statement 
   (Decision control statement)
      a. if statement
      syntax :    
            if(condition){
               .....
               .....
            }
      b. if else statement 
            if(condition){
               ......
            }else{
               ......
            }

      c. nested if else statement
      syntax : 
         i. if(condition){
               ....
            }else{
               if(condition){
                  ....
               }else{
                  
               }
            }

         ii. if(condition){
               if(condition){
                  ....
               }else{
                  
               }
            }else{
               ....
            }

         iii. if(condition){
                  if(condition){
                  ....
                  }else{
                     
                  }
               }else{
                  if(condition){
                  ....
                  }else{
                     
                  }
               }

      d. else if ladder 
         syntax:
               if(condition)
                  .....
               else if (condition)
                  .....
               else if (condition)
                  .....
               else  
                  .....

      
c. Switch control statement
   It is mainly  used for menu based programming.
   It works on the concept of cases.
   Duplicate cases not allowed.
   syntax :

         switch(constant | variable | expression){
            case 1 : ........
                     break;
            case '+' : ......
                     break;
            case 'a' : ......
                     break;
            case 'A' : ......
                     break;
            default : .......
                     break;
         } 

d. Looping control statement
   Looping is the process of performing same task or some task in an iterative manner untill certain condition is satisfied. 

   There are two types of loops : 
      a. Entry control loop 
      b. Exit control loop 

   a. Entry control loop 
      Where condition is checked at the time of entry.
      For loop and while loop comes under this category.
      
   b. Exit control loop
      Where condition is checked at the time of exit.
      do while loop comes under this category.
      

   For loop : When we already know in advance that how many times we have to exxecute our loop, then in that case we use for loop. 
   ex: table of a number 

   While loop : When we do not know in advance that how many times we have to execute our loop, then in that case we use while loop.
   ex : reversing a number 

   do while loop : Whether condition is true or false, do while loop may executes atleast once.  

   for each loop | advanced loop

   Syntax for for loop : 

                  step 1         step 2     step 3
         for ( initialization ; condition ; inc|dec )
         {
            ...........
            ...........
         }

   syntax for while loop : 

         initialization;

         while(condition){
             .........
             .........
             inc | dec;
         }

   syntax for do while loop : 

         initialization;

         do{
            .........
            .........
            inc | dec;
         }while(condition);
         
---------------------------------------------------------------------
ASCII VALUE 
-----------
American Standard Code for Information Interchannge 

A = 65      a = 97     0 = 48
B = 66      b = 98     1 = 49
|   |       |   |      |   |
Z = 90      z = 122    9 = 57

ch = sc.next().charAt(0);

if(ch>='A' && ch<='Z')
   uppercase
else {
   if(ch>=97 && ch<=122)
      lowercase
   else{
      if(ch>=48 && ch<=57)
         digit
      else
         invalid
   }
}